---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const CAL_URL = "https://cal.com/isabella-rondon-jrkvbh/30min";
---

<Layout
  title="Financial Data Infrastructure for B2B Services — Case Study"
  description="I rebuilt how a B2B financial services company managed reconciliation and client data — eliminating multi-day meetings, cutting errors 99%, and creating a single source of truth across four departments."
>

  <!-- CASE STUDY HEADER -->
  <header class="cs-header">
    <div class="cs-header-inner">
      <a href="/case-studies" class="cs-back">← Case Studies</a>
      <div class="cs-tag">Data Strategy · Workflow Automation</div>
      <h1 class="cs-headline">
        Days of reconciliation. Departments working from different numbers.<br>
        <span style="color: var(--accent-light);">I built the infrastructure that replaced all of it.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-subheadline">A B2B financial services company with 400+ corporate clients was running critical operations on manual exports, siloed spreadsheets, and informal messaging channels. I rebuilt how they managed their data from the ground up.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- STATS BAR -->
  <div class="cs-stats-bar">
    <div class="cs-stat-item">
      <div class="cs-stat-value">Days → &lt;1hr</div>
      <div class="cs-stat-label">reconciliation time</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-stat-divider"></div>
    <div class="cs-stat-item">
      <div class="cs-stat-value">99%</div>
      <div class="cs-stat-label">reduction in reconciliation errors</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-stat-divider"></div>
    <div class="cs-stat-item">
      <div class="cs-stat-value">100%</div>
      <div class="cs-stat-label">client satisfaction score</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- RESULTS TABLE — proof-first -->
  <section class="cs-results-summary">
    <div class="cs-results-summary-label">Before &amp; After</div>
    <div class="cs-results-table">
      <div class="cs-results-header">
        <span>Metric</span>
        <span>Before</span>
        <span>After</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-results-row">
        <span class="cs-metric"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg></span>Reconciliation time</span>
        <span>Hours — sometimes days</span>
        <span class="after">Under 1 hour</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-results-row">
        <span class="cs-metric"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg></span>Reconciliation error rate</span>
        <span>Frequent, cross-departmental</span>
        <span class="after">99% reduction</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-results-row">
        <span class="cs-metric"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="23 4 23 10 17 10"/><polyline points="1 20 1 14 7 14"/><path d="M3.51 9a9 9 0 0 1 14.85-3.36L23 10M1 14l4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0 0 20.49 15"/></svg></span>Data latency</span>
        <span>Manual exports, days old</span>
        <span class="after">Real-time, automated</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-results-row">
        <span class="cs-metric"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/><path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3"/><path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"/></svg></span>Data source</span>
        <span>Four teams, four spreadsheets</span>
        <span class="after">One source of truth</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="cs-closing-bold" style="margin-top: 28px;">Multi-day reconciliation meetings — eliminated. Four teams arguing about whose numbers were right — replaced by one automated infrastructure everyone trusts.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- TWO-COLUMN: NARRATIVE LEFT · SIDEBAR RIGHT -->
  <div class="cs-two-col">

    <!-- LEFT: narrative -->
    <div class="cs-two-col-main">

      <section class="cs-section">
        <h2 class="cs-section-title">The Problem</h2>
        <div class="cs-body">
          <p>Every transaction at this company involved multiple parties: an OTC provider, an operations team, and a finance department. The workflow holding it all together was informal by design — conversations happened over messaging apps, each department manually downloaded their piece of the data into their own spreadsheet, and nobody was working from the same numbers.</p>
          <p>When operations and finance sat down to reconcile, they weren't comparing data. They were arguing about whose version was correct. Those meetings regularly stretched from hours into days.</p>
          <p>One root cause: no reliable data infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="cs-section">
        <h2 class="cs-section-title">The Solution</h2>
        <div class="cs-body">
          <p>I built an automated workflow that replaced the informal messaging chain entirely. The informal channels closed, the data discrepancies disappeared, and reconciliation stopped being a multi-day negotiation.</p>

          <div class="cs-decisions">
            <div class="cs-decision-title">Key design decisions</div>
            <div class="cs-decision-item">
              <div class="cs-decision-name"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="6" y1="3" x2="6" y2="15"/><circle cx="18" cy="6" r="3"/><circle cx="6" cy="18" r="3"/><path d="M18 9a9 9 0 0 1-9 9"/></svg></span>Multi-party routing</div>
              <div class="cs-decision-desc">When a transaction came in, the relevant information was routed simultaneously to the right stakeholders — operations, finance, and the OTC provider — with no manual handoffs.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-decision-item">
              <div class="cs-decision-name"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg></span>Confidentiality between parties (RBAC)</div>
              <div class="cs-decision-desc">Each party saw only what they needed, with full confidentiality maintained between OTC partners.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-decision-item">
              <div class="cs-decision-name"><span class="cs-row-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/><path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3"/><path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"/></svg></span>Real-time sync to single source of truth</div>
              <div class="cs-decision-desc">Every transaction automatically populated a centralized Google Sheet — one source of truth, all departments, real time.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT: sticky sidebar -->
    <div class="cs-two-col-sidebar">

      <div class="cs-sidebar-card">
        <div class="cs-sidebar-label">What Was Built</div>
        <div class="cs-sidebar-tags">
          <span>Multi-party workflow automation</span>
          <span>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</span>
          <span>Single source of truth</span>
          <span>Real-time transaction logging</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-sidebar-cta">
        <p>Running critical operations on scattered data and informal channels?</p>
        <a href={CAL_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener">See if this fits your team →</a>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- CTA BLOCK -->
  <div class="cs-cta-block">
    <div class="cs-cta-inner">
      <div class="cs-cta-left">
        <h2 class="cs-cta-headline">Bad data costs more than you think — in time, in errors, and in decisions made on the wrong numbers.</h2>
        <p class="cs-cta-sub">If your team is working from siloed spreadsheets, manual exports, or informal data flows, the problem isn't just operational. It's commercial.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-cta-right">
        <a href={CAL_URL} class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a Discovery Call &nbsp;→</a>
        <span class="cta-note">No commitment. 30 minutes.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>
